name: "Red Team Engagement — Sovereign Trace Protocol"
description: "Seal the scope, methodology, and rules of engagement for a red team exercise before it begins. Proves what was authorized to test."
title: "[STP-REDTEAM] — [TARGET SYSTEM] — [DATE]"
labels: ["red-team", "pending-seal"]
assignees: []
body:
  - type: markdown
    attributes:
      value: |
        ## Red Team Engagement – Sovereign Trace Protocol (FROZEN‑4.0)

        This form seals the scope, methodology, and rules of engagement for a red team security exercise **before** it begins.

        When the engagement is complete, seal findings separately using `vulnerability-timeline.yml`. The pair of seals proves the engagement was honest and within authorized bounds.

        **⚠️ CRITICAL WARNINGS – READ BEFORE PROCEEDING ⚠️**
        - The scope and attack vectors are **public** and **permanent**.
        - Your GitHub username is **publicly linked** to this seal.
        - **Do not include live credentials, internal IP addresses, or non‑public system details.**
        - **Do not edit this issue after the workflow seals it** – the hash will change.
        - **This record is retained permanently** in the STP ledger and GitHub issue history.
        - A correction creates a new entry; the original remains.

        **Fields marked with `*` are required.**

  - type: input
    id: submitter_name
    attributes:
      label: "Your Name (Optional)"
      description: "If provided, becomes part of the permanent record. Leave blank for an anonymous seal."
      placeholder: "First Last or leave blank"
    validations:
      required: false

  - type: input
    id: target_system
    attributes:
      label: "Target System / Organization *"
      description: "The system, application, or organization being tested."
      placeholder: "e.g., Internal API Gateway, customer‑facing web app"
    validations:
      required: true

  - type: input
    id: engagement_period_start
    attributes:
      label: "Engagement Start Date *"
      placeholder: "2026-06-04"
    validations:
      required: true

  - type: input
    id: engagement_period_end
    attributes:
      label: "Engagement End Date *"
      placeholder: "2026-06-18"
    validations:
      required: true

  - type: textarea
    id: attack_vectors
    attributes:
      label: "Authorized Attack Vectors *"
      description: "List the specific attack methods permitted. One per line. Keep under 5,000 characters."
      placeholder: "SQL injection on public forms\nXSS on user‑generated content\nSSRF on internal endpoints\nSocial engineering via email (mock only, no real users)"
    validations:
      required: true

  - type: textarea
    id: prohibited_actions
    attributes:
      label: "Prohibited Actions *"
      description: "Explicitly list what is NOT allowed. One per line. Keep under 5,000 characters."
      placeholder: "No destruction of data\nNo privilege escalation beyond read‑only\nNo physical intrusion"
    validations:
      required: true

  - type: textarea
    id: team_members
    attributes:
      label: "Team Members (Optional)"
      description: "Names or roles of red team participants."
      placeholder: "Alice (lead), Bob (network), Charlie (app)"
    validations:
      required: false

  - type: textarea
    id: supporting_urls
    attributes:
      label: "Supporting Files URLs (Optional)"
      description: "Rules of engagement document, signed authorization, etc. Permanent URLs only."
      placeholder: "https://ipfs.io/ipfs/Qm..."
    validations:
      required: false

  - type: textarea
    id: supporting_hashes
    attributes:
      label: "Supporting file SHA‑256 hashes (optional, recommended)"
      description: "One SHA‑256 hash per file, in the same order as the URLs."
      placeholder: "a3f9c12e7d..."
    validations:
      required: false

  - type: input
    id: correction_of
    attributes:
      label: "Correction / Resubmission of (optional)"
      placeholder: "#42 or a3f9c12e7d..."
    validations:
      required: false

  - type: checkboxes
    id: declaration
    attributes:
      label: "Declaration *"
      options:
        - label: "I affirm that this engagement scope is authorized by the target organization and will be conducted lawfully."
          required: true
        - label: "I affirm that the listed prohibited actions will not be attempted under any circumstances."
          required: true
        - label: "I understand this submission is immutable — a correction creates a new entry but does not delete the original."
          required: true
        - label: "I understand that the attack vectors and prohibited actions are public."
          required: true

  - type: markdown
    attributes:
      value: |
        ---
        **After submission**: Seal findings separately with `vulnerability-timeline.yml` after engagement ends.

        **Contact:** `aionsystem@outlook.com`
